ISLAMABAD, June 24 (APP): Renowned calamity writer Imran Malik on Monday presented his book ‘Pakistan Earthquake  2005’ to Chairman Higher  Education  Commission Prof Mukhtar Ahmed in Islamabad.
The book is about the horrors of 7.6 magnitude earthquake that had struck the country leaving over 70,000 dead.
